{"parse":{"title":"Valsalva device","pageid":42554156,"revid":810287197,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux\" style=\"display:none\">Pad in a helmet or mask used to block the nose to assist in ear clearing </div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg/220px-Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg/330px-Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg/440px-Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2126\" data-file-height=\"1417\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Samantha_Cristoforetti_demonstrating_Valsalva_device.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Samantha Cristoforetti demonstrating the use of the Valsalva device in the Sokol space suit</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Valsalva device</b> is a device used in <a href=\"/wiki/Spacesuit\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spacesuit\">spacesuits</a>, some <a href=\"/wiki/Full_face_diving_mask\" title=\"Full face diving mask\">full face diving masks</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Diving_helmet\" title=\"Diving helmet\">diving helmets</a> to allow <a href=\"/wiki/Astronaut\" title=\"Astronaut\">astronauts</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Commercial_diver\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Commercial diver\">commercial divers</a> to equalize the pressure in their ears by performing the <a href=\"/wiki/Valsalva_maneuver\" title=\"Valsalva maneuver\">Valsalva maneuver</a> inside the suit without using their hands to block their nose. Astronaut <a href=\"/wiki/Drew_Feustel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Drew Feustel\">Drew Feustel</a> has described it as \"a spongy device called a Valsalva that is typically used to block the nose in case a pressure readjustment is needed.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-spacenews999_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-spacenews999-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-divernet_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-divernet-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In November 2011 <a href=\"/wiki/ESA\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ESA\">ESA</a> astronaut <a href=\"/wiki/Samantha_Cristoforetti\" title=\"Samantha Cristoforetti\">Samantha Cristoforetti</a> posted on Twitter a picture of her demonstrating the use of the Valsalva device in the <a href=\"/wiki/Sokol_space_suit\" title=\"Sokol space suit\">Sokol space suit</a> during suit pressurization.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Valsalva device has also been used for other purposes. On 25 May 2011, <a href=\"/wiki/NASA\" title=\"NASA\">NASA</a> reported that during the second spacewalk of <a href=\"/wiki/Space_Shuttle\" title=\"Space Shuttle\">Space Shuttle</a> mission <a href=\"/wiki/STS-134\" title=\"STS-134\">STS-134</a>, Feustel was able to clear tears from his eye by wiggling down far enough in his <a href=\"/wiki/Extravehicular_Mobility_Unit\" title=\"Extravehicular Mobility Unit\">Extravehicular Mobility Unit</a> to make use the Valsalva device in his suit as a sponge to clear up <a href=\"/wiki/Tears\" title=\"Tears\">tears</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-spacenews999_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-spacenews999-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> caused because anti-fogging agent (liquid soap) came free from the inside of the helmet and floated into his eye.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Valsalva_device&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-spacenews999-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-spacenews999_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-spacenews999_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.space-travel.com/reports/US_astronaut_grapples_with_tears_in_space_999.html\">\"US astronaut grapples with 'tears in space<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">'</span>\"</a>. <i>spacedaily.com</i>. 25 May 2011<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 May</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=spacedaily.com&amp;rft.atitle=US+astronaut+grapples+with+%27tears+in+space%27&amp;rft.date=2011-05-25&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.space-travel.com%2Freports%2FUS_astronaut_grapples_with_tears_in_space_999.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AValsalva+device\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-divernet-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-divernet_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Sibley-Calder, Ian. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.divernet.com/other_diving_topics/160154/q_amp_a_medical_0502.html\">\"Q &amp; A Medical 05/02 - Divernet\"</a>. Diver Magazine<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 April</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Q+%26+A+Medical+05%2F02+-+Divernet&amp;rft.pub=Diver+Magazine&amp;rft.aulast=Sibley-Calder&amp;rft.aufirst=Ian&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.divernet.com%2Fother_diving_topics%2F160154%2Fq_amp_a_medical_0502.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AValsalva+device\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Sam Cristoforetti [@AstroSamantha] (22 November 2011). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://twitter.com/AstroSamantha/status/138912801153490944\">\"It's a Valsalva device, to equalize ears as pressure in suit increases\"</a> (Tweet)<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 November</span> 2012</span>  &#8211; via <a href=\"/wiki/Twitter\" title=\"Twitter\">Twitter</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=It%27s+a+Valsalva+device%2C+to+equalize+ears+as+pressure+in+suit+increases&amp;rft.date=2011-11-22&amp;rft.au=Sam+Cristoforetti+%5B%40AstroSamantha%5D&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAstroSamantha%2Fstatus%2F138912801153490944&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AValsalva+device\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>    </span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Valsalva_device&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"e